@ThinkingandTinkering thank you for everything.
I hope you & your family are staying strong despite difficult times.
Please don’t stop doing what you do.

@raloed.363 I think there may be a simpler method than a toroid.  
I mean, we know that containing magnetic flux in a simple metal armature is doable- both in the switchable magnets and, say, a transformer.  It just seems like surely you could use that sort of concept to at least cut way down on the back emf and reduce if not eliminate the torque necessary for generation.

of course if that Was possible somebody probably would have thought of that by now.

@IanBarnfield  did you measure the 200w or is that an idealised estimate? 
I have a strong feeling that humans aren't capable of that much. 
I'm not basing that on facts though. Just a feeling
